'''''Alyzon Whitestarr''''' is a 2005 [[young-adult fiction|young-adult]] novel by [[Isobelle Carmody]]. It follows the story Alyzon Whitestarr who after an event can smell people's feelings, view flashes of their lives and perceive their essences. With these new senses she discovers that some peoples spirits have been infected by a sentient disease.<ref name="P AW">{{cite web | url = http://www.penguin.com.au/lookinside/spotlight.cfm?SBN=9780143002437 | title = Alyzon Whitestarr by Isobelle Carmody | publisher = [[Penguin Books]] | date = | accessdate = 2010-02-01}}</ref>

==Background==
''Alyzon Whitestarr'' was first published in Australia on September 26, 2005 by [[Penguin Books]] in [[trade paperback]] format.<ref name="ISFDB AW">{{cite web | url = http://www.isfdb.org/cgi-bin/title.cgi?196973 | title = Bibliography: Alyzon Whitestarr | publisher = [[ISFDB]] | date = | accessdate = 2010-02-01}}</ref> It was released by [[Random House]] in the United States in 2005.<ref name="WC AW">{{cite web | url = http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/247439100/editions?editionsView=true&referer=br | title = Formats and Editions of Alyzon Whitestarr | publisher = [[WorldCat]] | date = | accessdate = 2010-02-01}}</ref> ''Alyzon Whitestarr'' won the 2005 [[Aurealis Award for best young-adult novel]] and the 2005 [[Golden Aurealis for best novel]].<ref name="LO 2006AA">{{cite web | url = http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Aurealis2006.html | title = The Locus Index to SF Awards: 2006 Aurealis Awards | publisher = [[Locus Online]] | date = | accessdate = 2010-02-01}}</ref>

